// Traffic To or From the capturing computer IPv4 address:
//   Local <-> Any
// If you have more than one network adapter, this becomes
// an array, indexed starting from zero.  This requires that the
// NetworkInfo packet is captured in the trace.

IPv4.address == Global.IpConfig.LocalIpv4Address

// Traffic To or From the capturing computer IPv6 address:
//   Local <-> Any
// If you have more than one network adapter, this becomes
// an array, indexed starting from zero.

// IPv6.Address == Global.IpConfig.LocalIpv6Address

// Example when there are multiple adapters.  This
// filters on the second adapters address listed in the
// NetworkInfo frame.

// IPv4.Address == Global.IpConfig.LocalIpv4Address[1]